   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Through the presbyteroi of the village of Philadelphia. Sarapion, son of Sarapion, has paid to Mendes, son of Kephalos, for the tax on transport of sheaves and sacks of the 20th year of Marcus Aurelius Severus Antoninus, Pauni 11, four &lt;drachmai&gt; on account, 4 dr.</ab>
